@page "/docs/api"

<PageTitle>API reference — DigiPay</PageTitle>

<div class="min-h-dvh flex flex-col bg-slate-50 dark:bg-dgb-950 text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-sans">
    <SiteNav />

    <main class="flex-1">
        <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-8 sm:py-12">
            <h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-2">API reference</h1>
            <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-8">
                DigiPay speaks plain REST. All endpoints live under <InlineCode>/v1/pay</InlineCode>.
                Authenticated endpoints take a Bearer API key that DigiPay mints for you when you
                sign in with Digi-ID.
            </p>

            <DocsHeading>Authentication</DocsHeading>
            <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-3">Every merchant-scoped endpoint requires a Bearer token in the <InlineCode>Authorization</InlineCode> header:</p>
            <CodeBlock>Authorization: Bearer dgp_@("{prefix}_{secret}")</CodeBlock>
            <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mt-3">Get your key from the merchant dashboard after signing in with Digi-ID. The token is stored hashed server-side (SHA-256) and compared in constant time; losing it is equivalent to losing your API access, not your funds.</p>

            <DocsHeading>Sessions</DocsHeading>

            <Endpoint Method="POST" Path="/v1/pay/sessions">
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 m-0 mb-3">Create a new payment session. Returns a session record including a <InlineCode>checkout_url</InlineCode> you can redirect buyers to.</p>
                <CodeBlock>@("{\n  \"amount\": 12.5,               // required, DGB\n  \"label\": \"Order #4201\",       // optional, shown on checkout\n  \"memo\": \"inv-001\",            // optional, merchant-private invoice number\n  \"fiatCurrency\": \"USD\",        // optional, not yet enforced by price lock\n  \"fiatAmount\": 5.00,           // optional\n  \"expiresInSeconds\": 1800      // optional, overrides merchant default\n}")</CodeBlock>
                <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mt-3">Response includes the derived <InlineCode>address</InlineCode>, a BIP21 <InlineCode>uri</InlineCode>, the hosted <InlineCode>checkoutUrl</InlineCode>, and <InlineCode>expiresAt</InlineCode>.</p>
            </Endpoint>

            <Endpoint Method="GET" Path="/v1/pay/sessions">
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 m-0">List your sessions, newest first. Supports <InlineCode>?status=pending|seen|paid|confirmed|expired|underpaid</InlineCode>, <InlineCode>?take=1..100</InlineCode> (default 25), <InlineCode>?skip=0..</InlineCode>.</p>
            </Endpoint>

            <Endpoint Method="GET" Path="/v1/pay/sessions/{id}">
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 m-0">Public read of a session's current state. No auth required — the session id is random and contains no secret. Used by the hosted checkout page.</p>
            </Endpoint>

            <DocsHeading>Merchant profile</DocsHeading>

            <Endpoint Method="GET" Path="/v1/pay/me">
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 m-0">Returns the authenticated merchant: id, display name, Digi-ID address, receive mode, webhook config, default expiry.</p>
            </Endpoint>

            <Endpoint Method="PATCH" Path="/v1/pay/me">
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 m-0 mb-3">Update any subset of:</p>
                <CodeBlock>@("{\n  \"displayName\": \"My Shop\",\n  \"addressOrXpub\": \"xpub6...\",         // or \"dgb1...\"\n  \"network\": \"mainnet\",                // mainnet | testnet | regtest\n  \"webhookUrl\": \"https://...\",         // auto-generates a secret on first set\n  \"defaultSessionExpiryMinutes\": 45    // 1..1440\n}")</CodeBlock>
            </Endpoint>

            <Endpoint Method="GET" Path="/v1/pay/me/donation-address">
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 m-0">Returns a stable address for donation buttons. In xpub mode this is derive index 0 (reserved — invoice sessions start at index 1). In address mode it's the configured address.</p>
            </Endpoint>

            <Endpoint Method="POST" Path="/v1/pay/me/webhook/test">
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 m-0">Fires a synthetic <InlineCode>webhook.test</InlineCode> event at your configured webhook URL. Useful for verifying your HMAC check.</p>
            </Endpoint>

            <DocsHeading>Webhooks</DocsHeading>
            <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-3">DigiPay POSTs signed JSON to your configured <InlineCode>webhookUrl</InlineCode> on every state change. Fire-and-forget, 10-second timeout, no retries yet — treat the webhook as a hint, always confirm state by calling <InlineCode>GET /v1/pay/sessions/{id}</InlineCode> if your logic is money-critical.</p>
            <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mt-3 mb-2">Body:</p>
            <CodeBlock>@("{\n  \"event\": \"session.paid\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-19T12:34:56Z\",\n  \"session\": {\n    \"id\": \"ses_...\",\n    \"merchantId\": \"mer_...\",\n    \"address\": \"dgb1q...\",\n    \"amountSatoshis\": 1250000000,\n    \"amount\": 12.5,\n    \"status\": \"paid\",\n    \"receivedSatoshis\": 1250000000,\n    \"confirmations\": 1,\n    \"paidTxid\": \"...\",\n    \"createdAt\": \"...\",\n    \"expiresAt\": \"...\"\n  }\n}")</CodeBlock>

            <h3 class="text-base font-bold mt-6 mb-2 tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Signature verification</h3>
            <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-3">Compute <InlineCode>HMAC_SHA256(secret, rawBody)</InlineCode> as hex, prefix with <InlineCode>sha256=</InlineCode>, and constant-time compare with the incoming <InlineCode>X-DigiPay-Signature</InlineCode> header. Example in Node:</p>
            <CodeBlock>@("const crypto = require('crypto');\n\napp.post('/webhook', express.raw({ type: 'application/json' }), (req, res) => {\n  const expected = 'sha256=' +\n    crypto.createHmac('sha256', process.env.DIGIPAY_SECRET)\n          .update(req.body).digest('hex');\n  const provided = req.headers['x-digipay-signature'];\n  if (!crypto.timingSafeEqual(Buffer.from(expected), Buffer.from(provided))) {\n    return res.status(401).end();\n  }\n  const event = JSON.parse(req.body.toString());\n  // ... reconcile event.session.id in your database ...\n  res.status(200).end();\n});")</CodeBlock>

            <DocsHeading>Embed widget</DocsHeading>
            <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-3">The JS embed is hosted at <InlineCode>/embed/digipay.js</InlineCode>. ~7 KB, no dependencies, derives its own origin from the script src.</p>
            <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-2">Programmatic:</p>
            <CodeBlock>@("DigiPay.checkout({ sessionId: 'ses_abc' });  // opens iframe modal\nDigiPay.close();                              // dismiss it\nconst a = DigiPay.button({ address: 'dgb1...', amount: 5, name: 'Shop' });\ndocument.body.appendChild(a);")</CodeBlock>
            <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mt-3 mb-2">Declarative:</p>
            <CodeBlock>@("<button data-digipay-checkout data-session-id=\"ses_abc\">Pay</button>\n<span data-digipay-button data-address=\"dgb1...\" data-amount=\"5\">Tip</span>")</CodeBlock>
            <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mt-3">Auto-binds on <InlineCode>DOMContentLoaded</InlineCode>; call <InlineCode>DigiPay.bind(rootEl)</InlineCode> after injecting new elements dynamically.</p>

            <DocsHeading>Status codes</DocsHeading>
            <ul class="space-y-1 leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 list-disc pl-5">
                <li><InlineCode>200</InlineCode> — success.</li>
                <li><InlineCode>400</InlineCode> — validation error, body includes an <InlineCode>error</InlineCode> field.</li>
                <li><InlineCode>401</InlineCode> — missing or invalid Bearer token.</li>
                <li><InlineCode>404</InlineCode> — session / endpoint not found.</li>
                <li><InlineCode>409</InlineCode> — challenge already resolved (Digi-ID flows).</li>
            </ul>

            <DocsHeading>Questions?</DocsHeading>
            <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">The source is open. Clone the repo, file an issue, or just run DigiPay yourself — it's designed to self-host in a single container with a SQLite file.</p>
        </article>
    </main>

    <SiteFooter />
</div>
